== Potato Slices ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 375 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges.

Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}(picked and roughly chopped).

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, half the dill, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until potatoes are lightly browned and tender, ~potatoes{30-35%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}; cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

== Prep ==

While potatoes roast, zest @lemon{1} and halve lengthwise; thinly slice half the lemon into half-moons. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Peel and thinly slice @garlic{2%clove}. Halve @tomato{1} lengthwise, then thinly slice into half-moons. Trim and slice @zucchini{2} crosswise into ½-inch-thick rounds.

== Fish ==

Pat @Open Blue Cobia{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and place in a large #bowl{}.

Season cobia with a drizzle of olive oil, lemon zest, remaining dill, salt, and pepper. Rub to evenly coat fish.

== Assembly ==

Cut two 10-inch-long pieces of #parchment paper{} or #foil{} (four pieces of parchment or foil for 4 servings); arrange pieces on a work surface with a long side facing you.

Dividing evenly, arrange shallot lengthwise in the center of parchment or foil pieces. Top with garlic and tomato. Season with salt and pepper.

Lay seasoned cobia on top of tomato. Shingle as many lemon half-moons as you like on top of fish, then top each with @butter{2%tablespoon}.

For each cobia oven packet, bring the two long sides of parchment or foil toward the center and fold down several times until there is about 1 inch of space between parchment or foil and fish and the seal is secure.

Roll the shorter ends of parchment or foil tightly to seal packets.

> Tightly sealing the packets will ensure that the fish steams properly.

Set aside.

== Zucchini and Baking ==

Place zucchini in a second large bowl. Toss with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Arrange zucchini on one side of a second baking sheet in a single overlapping layer.

> Be sure to shingle the zucchini in a single layer so they cook evenly.

Place cobia oven packets on empty side of baking sheet.

Roast on middle rack until zucchini is tender and cobia is fully cooked, ~zucchini and fish{18-20%minutes}.

== Dijonnaise ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon} and @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}.

== To Serve ==

Divide cobia oven packets, potatoes, and zucchini between plates. Carefully cut a 3-inch slit in top of packets alongside the fold.

> If cobia isn't fully cooked yet, carefully return opened packets to baking sheet and roast for a few more minutes.

Serve with Dijonnaise for dipping and remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> When you're ready to eat, gently pull the oven packets apart at slit to open (careful—steam will be released) and push aside the lemon slices!

> Cobia is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.